'''Red Oxx Manufacturing, Inc.''' is an [[United States|American]] manufacturing company which produces travel luggage.<ref>{{citation|title=TED ANDERSON, VENTURES WEST PRESIDENT|work=[[The Globe and Mail]]|date= December 6, 2006|url= https://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/LAC.20061206.EXEC06/TPStory/Travel}}</ref><ref>{{citation|title=RED OXX CARRY-ON|publisher= [[St. Paul Pioneer Press]] |date=June 18, 2006 |url=http://docs.newsbank.com/g/GooglePM/SP/lib00247,11268E63C69BD178.html}}</ref> The company was founded in 1986 by Jim Markel Sr., a retired [[United States Army Special Forces|Green Beret]] [[Captain (OF-2)|Captain]], and was joined by his son Jim Markel Jr. and Perry Jones, also retired military parachute riggers.<ref>[http://www.redoxx.com/misc/our-story.tpl Red Oxx history]</ref> In the U.S., the products have won a  'National Award for Luggage'.<ref>{{citation|title=Billings, Mont., Company Bags National Award for Luggage|publisher= [[Billings Gazette]] |date= April 15, 2004|quote=Outside Buyer's Guide has selected a bag made by Red Oxx Manufacturing|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-118297944.html?refid=gg_x_02}}</ref> Also, the Red Oxx Safari Beano bag was [[Outside Magazine]]'s 2004 Bag of the Year.<ref>[http://outside.away.com/outside/gear/gear.tcl?gear=Red-Oxx-PR5-Safari-Beano-s-Bag&gear_id=218&action=showgear 2004 Bag of the Year]  [[Outside Magazine]]</ref>

